
[1]oblivion

   OBLIV'ION, n. [L. oblivio.]

   1. Forgetfulness; cessation of remembrance.

   Among our crimes oblivion may be set.

   2. A forgetting of offenses, or remission of punishment. An act of
   oblivion is an amnesty, or general pardon of crimes and offenses,
   granted by a sovereign, by which punishment is remitted.
